# Important basics

## URL layout (client + server must match)

| Transport | Base | Example |
|-----------|------|---------|
| REST | `{SERVER_DOMAIN}/api/` | `GET /api/workspaces/` |
| WebSocket | `{SERVER_DOMAIN}/api/ws/` | `wss://…/api/ws/sync/1/?…` |

Flutter source of truth: `app/lib/core/config/app_config.dart`

- `apiBaseUrl` → `https://{host}/api/`
- `webSocketUri(relativePath)` → `wss://{host}/api/ws/{relativePath}` (trailing `/` before `?`)
- `webSocketSyncUri(workspaceId)` → `/api/ws/sync/{id}/`
- Never build WS URLs with string concat + `Uri.parse` (causes `:0` port bugs). Use `AppConfig.webSocketUri` / `webSocketSyncUri`.
- Never omit `port` on WebSocket `Uri` on mobile — use explicit **443** (wss) or **80** (ws); omitted port can become `:0` on Android.

Server WebSocket routes: `server/config/routing.py` — all under `api/ws/…`.

## REST authentication

Implemented in `server/core/authentication.py` (`DeviceAPIKeyAuthentication`).

Required headers on every REST call except `/api/health/` and `POST /api/devices/register/`:

```
X-API-Key: {settings.API_KEY}          # must match .env API_KEY
X-Device-Identifier: {device_hash}     # SHA256 from device registration
X-Workspace-Id: {id}                 # required for workspace-scoped endpoints
```

Flutter: `app/lib/core/api/api_client.dart` attaches these via Dio interceptor.

Workspace-scoped views use `RequiresWorkspace` (`server/core/permissions.py`) — resolves workspace from `X-Workspace-Id` header.

HTTP middleware (`server/core/middleware.py`) **skips** `/api/ws/*` — those paths are not REST; auth is on the WebSocket layer only.

## WebSocket authentication

Implemented in `server/core/ws_auth.py` (`DeviceAuthWsMiddleware`).

Auth via **query string** on connect (same credentials as REST):

```
?api_key=…&device_hash=…&workspace_id=…
```

Flutter: `app/lib/core/ws/ws_client.dart` — use `connectSync(workspaceId)` or `connect(relativePath)`; both add auth query params.

Unauthenticated WS → close `4401`. Wrong workspace → `4403`/`4404`.

## Server runtime

- **ASGI only** — no `wsgi.py`; entry point is `config.asgi.application` (`ASGI_APPLICATION` in settings).
- **`manage.py runserver`** serves ASGI (HTTP + WebSockets) because `daphne` is first in `INSTALLED_APPS`. Never use `--noasgi`.
- **uvicorn** is an optional production alternative: `uvicorn config.asgi:application --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000`.
- Requires `websockets` / `wsproto` when using uvicorn (`pip install -r server/requirements.txt`).
- HTTP middleware skips `/api/ws/*`; WS auth is query-string only (`core/ws_auth.py`).
- Public access via Cloudflare tunnel → `SERVER_DOMAIN` (default `aimaxx.organisationapp.online`).

## Workspace sync

- **Transport:** WebSocket only from the app (`/api/ws/sync/{id}/`).
- **Not** blocking HTTP `POST /api/workspaces/{id}/sync/` (legacy/tests only).
- Client: `WorkspaceSyncService` → `WsClient.connectSync()` → background via `workspaceSyncProvider`.
- Server: `files/consumers.py` (`WorkspaceSyncConsumer`).

## Defaults

- Server URL: `https://aimaxx.organisationapp.online`
- API key: must match server `.env` `API_KEY` (app default is placeholder `change-me-to-a-long-random-secret`)

When adding a new WS endpoint: update `server/config/routing.py`, add test under `server/tests/test_*_ws.py`, and extend `AppConfig` / `WsClient` — keep paths under `/api/ws/`.

## Remote desktop (WebRTC)

- Server capture: `server/remote/screen.py` (`mss` → `aiortc` `ScreenTrack`).
- Signaling: `server/remote/webrtc.py` + `remote/consumers.py` on `/api/ws/remote/`.
- Client video: `flutter_webrtc` in `app/lib/core/remote/remote_webrtc.dart`.
- Input: `input_batch` frames with `op` (`pointer_move`, `click`, `key_combo`); `REMOTE_INPUT_ENABLED` kill switch in `.env`.
- Tests set `REMOTE_WEBRTC_STUB=true` (no real peer negotiation).

